gtkspell
-------------------------------------------
GtkSpell provides word-processor-style highlighting and replacement of 
misspelled words in a GtkTextView widget. Right-clicking a misspelled 
word pops up a menu of suggested replacements.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  glib2-2.12.13-1
  gtk2-x11-2.10.14-1
  libaspell15-0.50.3-1
  libintl8-0.15-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  cygwin-1.5.24-2
  autoconf2.5-2.61-1
  automake1.9-1.9.6-2
  binutils-20060817-1
  cygport-0.3.5-1
  gawk-3.1.5-4
  gcc-core-3.4.4-3
  gettext-devel-0.15-1
  gtk-doc-1.8-1
  libtool1.5-1.5.23a-2
  make-3.81-1
  pkg-config-0.21-1
  sed-4.1.5-2

Canonical homepage:
  http://gtkspell.sourceforge.net/

Canonical download:
  http://gtkspell.sourceforge.net/download/

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  unpack gtkspell-2.0.11-X-src.tar.bz2
    if you use setup to install this src package, it will be
	 unpacked under /usr/src automatically
  cd /usr/src
  cygport ./gtkspell-2.0.11-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gtkspell-2.0.11-X-src.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/gtkspell-2.0.11-X.tar.bz2
  /usr/src/gtkspell-devel-2.0.11-X.tar.bz2

-------------------------------------------

